<h4>When using 'Demographics' parameters to filter search results</h4>
After executing a search, the 'Demographics' parameters are located on the lower left of the application. These may be used to filter a large number of records. There are some slight differences in the way these parameters perform compared to when they are used in 'Advanced Search'.
<br/>
<h5>Age Range</h5>
When filtering with the 'Age Range' parameter, the user must set <b>both</b> a lower and upper limit. Omitting one or the other will return a filter error.
<br/><br/>
Currently, this is the only demographic filter that works for Maui Firearms results.
<br/>
<h5>Race, Height, Weight</h5>
When filtering on Criminal History returns, these parameters perform as expected.
<br/><br/>
As mentioned previously, Warrants records do not have these attributes. Instead of ignoring these parameters as in 'Advanced Search', the 'Demographics' filter tries to (and fails) to find matching records. As such, no Warrant records will be returned whenever one of these parameters is used to filter.
<br/>
<h5>Race</h5>
Only 1 racial group may be selected from the dropdown.
<br/>
<h5>Height</h5>
When using 'Height', the 'feet', 'inches', and 'variance' (+/-) fields are all mandatory. The 'feet' field must be greater than 0. The 'inches' field must be 0 <= inches < 12.
<br/>
<h5>Weight</h5>
Likewise, when using weight, both the pounds and variance fields are mandatory.
<br/><br/>
<h5>Eye Color, Hair Color</h5>
Currently, these parameters are not supported for filtering as the current person search results format does not include hair and eye color.  This is a known issue and under review.
